<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2700">5.4. Setting up the listing scheduler</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>With plentymarkets, you can automatically place listings on the market at a certain time and you can automatically restart finished listings. Use the listing scheduler to set up these automatic procedures. Listings can be linked to several listing schedulers.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want plentymarkets to automatically start listings at a certain time, you can define time intervals in the listing scheduler. Either select <strong>days of the week</strong> or up to three <strong>days of the month</strong> in the listing scheduler. In both cases, you also have to choose <strong>starting times</strong> for the listing.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>The listing scheduler only adds a listing to the future listings if no entry exists for the MLID and if there is no active or hidden listing for this MLID.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>On eBay, a maximum of one auction with 0 bids can be visible at once.<br>
<strong><em>Example:</em></strong><br>
You have 10 active listings for a MLID. All listings have 0 bids. As such, only one of the 10 listings is visible to end customers.<br>
As soon as the offer receives its first bid, a new offer is published.<br>
As such, you then have 1 auction with 1 bid and 1 auction with 0 bids.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up the listing scheduler:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Listings » Scheduler</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Create new listing scheduler</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the desired settings. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#settings-scheduler">Table 15</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
