<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="3000">5.6.3. Importing layout templates</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can create and edit layout templates externally and then import these layout templates into plentymarkets. Layout templates are imported into your plentymarkets system with a ZIP file.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Importing layout templates:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Listings » Layouts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Import</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Import layout</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name for the new layout template.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Upload files</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the ZIP file that includes your layout template in the <strong>Upload files</strong> window.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open</strong>.<br>
→ The layout template is imported and displayed in the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
