<div class="title">Query update status</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can query the update status once you have begun updating the listings. In the group function window, click on <strong>Query update status</strong>. The results are displayed in a message.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> Only updates which contain more than 10 listings are displayed in this window. If you update fewer than 10 listings, then the listings will be updated synchronously.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="5900">18.3. Editing active listings with batch processing</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Batch processing includes the same options as the group function. However, the batch processing function edits previously filtered listings. The filters used for narrowing down listings are the same as described for search filters in <a href="#filter-options-listings">Table 21</a> and <a href="#filter-options-active-listings">Table 23</a>. The procedures are the same as described for group functions in <a href="#procedures-group-function">Table 24</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing active listings with batch processing:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Listings » Batch processing » Active listings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the filters. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#filter-options-listings">Table 21</a> and <a href="#filter-options-active-listings">Table 23</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to <a href="#aktionen-gruppenfunktion">[aktionen-gruppenfunktion]</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Execute</strong> to carry out the settings.<br>
→ A new notification window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Confirm the notification with <strong>Execute</strong> if the changes should be applied to all selected listings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="5950">19. Managing listing processes</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title"><strong>Listings » Listing processes</strong> currently without function</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Listings » Listing processes</strong> menu is currently being tested and therefore cannot be used at the moment. The menu’s functionalities will be activated as soon as the test phase has been completed.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Listings » Listing processes</strong> menu contains an overview of all listing processes that will be carried out in the future. Listing processes include all automatic processes which are carried out for listings, such as <strong>starting</strong>, <strong>updating</strong>, <strong>relisting</strong>, and <strong>ending</strong> listings. At present, this menu displays only listings that you have <em>started</em> individually or via group function. The menu also contains information about when the process was started and when it is estimated to be finished.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can open the item and the market listing from the overview to edit or check the settings. Moreover, you can use the group function to delete planned listing processes and thus prevent processes from being started.</p>
</div>
