<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="5960">19.2. Cancelling listing processes</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the group function to cancel multiple listing processes at once. First, select the processes that you would like to delete.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting listing processes with the group function:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Listings » Listing processes</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the processes that should be deleted.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open group function</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Group function</strong> area is expanded.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>Cancel processes</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Group function</strong> to delete the selected processes and thus cancel them from being started.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Deleting listings with endless lister</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you delete a listing that has the <strong>Endless lister</strong> option activated, then this listing is started again. In this case, you would not have prevented the listing from being started. In order to delete the listing, you have to deactivate the endless lister first.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
