</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="9300">27.2.3. Processing purchase cancellations: accept requests</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You have two possibilities to accept purchase cancellation requests: You can either change the order status or delete outstanding orders.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Refund</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If the item for which you accepted the purchase cancellation request was already paid for, then you have 10 days to refund the purchase price.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div id="9200" class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><em>Alternative 1:</em> Accepting requests - Changing the order status</div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you have linked the eBay purchase cancellation statuses with your own statuses yy#900, as described above&gt;&gt;, then purchase cancellation requests are imported with the status that you set for “eBay purchase cancellation requested”. By changing the order status, you can process each request individually.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Changing the order status to accept purchase cancellation:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Edit orders</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search for orders with the status for <strong>eBay purchase cancellation requested</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select an order.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Change the order’s status to the status for <strong>eBay purchase cancellation accepted</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ eBay will be automatically informed about your decision if you have set up the event procedure <a href="#9800">Communicating a purchase cancellation acceptance</a>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the group function to change multiple orders at once. If you want to accept the request for unpaid orders, then search for all unpaid orders with the appropriate status and change the orders’ status with the <a href="/en/orders/managing-orders#1700">group function</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It might be possible to set up an <a href="/en/automation/event-procedures">event procedure</a> based on your specific workflows that accepts requests automatically using certain filters.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><em>Alternative 2:</em> Accepting purchase cancellations - Deleting outstanding orders</div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Outstanding orders are those orders for which the buyer has not yet completed the checkout process on eBay. Outstanding orders are only displayed in plentymarkets if the <strong>Shipping costs for new orders coming from eBay</strong> option was set to <strong>Transfer from eBay</strong>. This option is found under <strong>Setup » Listings » Checkout</strong>. To accept a purchase cancellation request for an outstanding order, delete this outstanding order.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting outstanding orders to accept a purchase cancellation:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » eBay » Data exchange</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search for orders with the error message <strong>Purchase cancellation requested for this order</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select an order.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Delete the order.<br>
→ Your decision is sent to eBay even if no event procedure is set up.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="9400">27.2.4. Processing purchase cancellations: reject requests</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>There are two ways to reject requests: You can either change the order status or create an event procedure to automatically reject requests for cancelling paid orders.</p>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><em>Alternative 1:</em> Rejecting requests - Changing the order status</div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you have linked the eBay purchase cancellation statuses with your own statuses yy#900, as described above&gt;&gt;, then purchase cancellation requests are imported with the status that you set for “eBay purchase cancellation requested”. By changing the order status, you can process each request individually.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Changing the order status to reject requests:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Edit orders</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search for orders with the status for <strong>eBay purchase cancellation requested</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select an order.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Change the order’s status to the status for <strong>eBay purchase cancellation rejected</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ eBay will be automatically informed about your decision if you have set up the event procedure <a href="#9900">Communicating a purchase cancellation rejection</a>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><em>Alternative 2:</em> Automatically reject purchase cancellations for paid orders with an event procedure</div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up two <a href="/en/automation/event-procedures">event procedures</a> to always automatically reject purchase cancellation requests for paid orders.</p>
</div>
<div class="exampleblock collapseBox">
<div class="title">Setting up an event procedure</div>
<div class="content">
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Events</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add event procedure</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The <strong>Create new event procedure</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a distinct name for the event procedure.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>Event</strong> according to <a href="#mark-paid-orders">Table 50</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
