<h2 id="10000">28. Viewing the API log</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The menu <strong>Data » API log » Tab: API log</strong> contains a history of processes that run via the eBay interface. The following formats are available for eBay:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>EbayImportCancellations</strong> (import of cancellations)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>EbayFullfilment</strong> (payment confirmation, shipping confirmation)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>EBayImportReturns</strong> (import of returns)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>TimeAction_Action_Ebay</strong> (eBay procedure manager)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>EbayDispute</strong> (dispute processes)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>ItemListingControllerEBay</strong> (listings in general)</p>
</li>
<li>
